snippet.textDisplay: Cases in NY may be going up (more testing) but the U.S. fatality rate for covid-19 has dropped by half every 4-5 days since early March.  According to CDC data released 3/20, the fatality rate in the U.S. has dropped from 4.06 percent on March 8 (22 deaths of 541 cases) to 1.32 percent on March 20 (256 of 19,383 cases).  If we factor in all the cases we don't know about because the people recovered without going to the doctor, the fatality rate could reasonably drop to 1 to 1/2 percent - similar or less than the rate for influenza.  Wash your hands. Don't go to work if you're sick. Be sensible. Stop hoarding toilet paper.
